{"word":"κρόταφος","slug":"κρόταφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κρόταφος</b></el> <el>(κρότᾰφος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κροτέω'><el>κροτέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the side of the forehead</i> (<a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:κόρση'><el>κόρση</el></a>), in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>the temples</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>tempora</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of a mountain, <i>its side</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}